replies.body:
The elo system works great, it doesn't take "high diamond or challenger" as you put it to rank up quickly. If you are 3 divisions higher in skill than you are in current rank carrying is easy. The 2 division discrepancy that a player might have between skill/rank is a small issue and most certainly not worth changing the elo system for something else.

BTW making the system account for dc players would do nothing but bloat the ladder upwards, every game u keep your elo because of it has no value because every1 gained the same elo from other "dc loss prevented" scenarios. I won't address giving loss prevented to games where some1 had a bad score for obvious reasons.

{{champion:103}}
